data.value: Search System: Add @ at beginning to search by mod name. Add # at beginning to search by item ID. Add $ at beginning to search by mod ID. Use ; to split up search terms. Example: #minecraft;Block of Iron

data.name: label13.Text
data.value:
Welcome to Iridium! Here you can use the visual editor to create new recipes or remove preexisting ones.
How to get started:
Generating items: To generate items, you'll need this program's mod, Iridium Exporter (along with its dependency Architectury). Go into a world and run the command "/iridiumexporter export all" and let it generate all the files needed (If you don't want images, replace "all" with "itemdata"). Then just go into your Minecraft directory and drag the file titled "exporteddata" into the dropbox. Let the program load for a couple seconds and your items should be all loaded in!
Exporting Code: Go to the Export Tab and click on the "Export Code" Button. Save the file to somewhere you'll remember. Then, drag the file to your minecraft folder, then move it the selected mods scripts folder. Next time you reload or join a world you should notice the new recipes!

data.name: adaptiveRecipeLabel.Text
data.value: This program supports crafttweaker's adaptive shaped recipes (2x2, 1x3, etc.). If you wish to not have adaptive shaped recipes, please include air items in the empty slots. If you are creating a recipe like boots, you'll have to put air in between the items to prevent the program from snapping the ingredients together.
